Aaron Ramsey is in a race against time to get fit for Arsenal’s key clash with Manchester City on Saturday after suffering an ankle injury during Wales’s 2-1 victory over Andorra.

The midfielder was the victim of some roughhouse treatment and rolled his ankle after receiving a kick.

Manager Chris Coleman said the extent of the injury would be revealed in the next 24 hours leaving Arsene Wenger with a selection headache. 

