'There were half a dozen challenges that weren't very good. The ref should have clamped down but he let it go and we are a bit disappointed with that - we had a bit to contend with tonight.'

Arsenal host Manchester City at the Emirates Stadium at 12.45pm on Saturday, as the Premier League makes its return following the international break.

Gunners boss Arsene Wenger will be desperate for a fully fit squad as they welcome the champions to north London, hoping to pick up three points in a bid to assert themselves as title contenders.

